In Markdown, the structure is flat and linear. The h1 to h6 header doesn't "wrap" the text below it; it simply marks a point where a new section begins.

<existing>
h1:Instruction {
  p:this is a very strong:important instruction
  ul {
    li:step 1
    li:step 2
    li:step 3
  }
}
</existing>
<expect>
h1:Instruction
p:this is a very strong:important instruction
ul {
  li:step 1
  li:step 2
  li:step 3
}
</expect>
